# File: bigcam/usr/share/biglinux/bigcam/ui/about_dialog.py, line: 39
msgid   "The universal webcam control center for Linux.\n"
        "\n"
        "BigCam was born as a small shell script so that Rafael Ruscher could "
        "use his Canon Rebel T3 as a webcam during live streams about "
        "BigLinux. That humble hack, written by Rafael and Barnabé di "
        "Kartola, evolved from a Bash bridge between gPhoto2 and FFmpeg into "
        "a full GTK4/Adwaita application with live preview, multi-backend "
        "camera support (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP cameras, "
        "smartphones), real-time OpenCV effects, virtual camera output, photo "
        "and video capture, and 29 languages."
msgstr  ""

